==English==

===Etymology===
Reminiscent of a [[circus]] animal performing [[tricks]] by jumping through hoops.

===Verb===
{{en-verb|sg=[[jump]] [[through]] [[hoops]]|jumps through hoops|jumping through hoops|jumped through hoops}}
#{{idiom}} To put forth [[effort]] for the sake of [[appearance]] or [[demonstration]].
#:''They really made the salesman '''jump through hoops''' before buying anything.''